Government has been working hard to enforce strict measures during the lockdown. Some have been calling for government to lift the ban of alcohol and cigarettes. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Government has been working hard to enforce strict measures during the lockdown. Some have been calling for the government to lift the ban of alcohol and cigarettes. READ: Lockdown: SA air quality improves with less road traffic The chairperson of the Fair-Trade Independent Tobacco Association (Fita), Sinenhlanhla Mnguni says government must allow the sale of cigarettes.
“The fiscus is also losing billions of rand which if they will be collecting if legitimate manufactures were allowed to trade,” Mnguni said.
Mnguni said Fita was concerned at the sale of Vaping products despite a lockdown. The sale of cigarettes and alcohol has been prohibited as the country deals with the spread of COVID-19. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.